<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Levels have already killed PvP</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Azeraab">Azeraab</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:48 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Levels have already killed PvP<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>As many have noticed EQ is totally tied to level to the point where even a group of moderately high level characters cant kill something that is 3 or 4 levels higher than them simply because they will never hit it and it will resist all of their spells. Its the same with PvP, one 20th lvl player will easily wipe out dozens of 10th lvl players. Until this changes I really dont thing EQ will be a viable PvP game.

<P>At this point I think the tight tie of lvls with xp gains combined with the steep power increases of higher lvl monsters makes EQ a somewhat less than viable PvE game. It certainly keeps it from being very entertaining.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
